metadata.name: Monalisa Moon Mission 38x48cm Digital Painting
metadata.description:
15x19 inch, 300DPI, [Digital Art](https://arth2o.ie/) #original #earthbg edition from [Bitcoin Art Gallery](https://bitcoinart.net/).
--
Mona Lisa, also called Portrait of Lisa Gherardini, wife of Francesco del Giocondo, Italian La Gioconda, or French La Joconde, oil painting on a poplar wood panel by Leonardo da Vinci, probably the world's most famous painting.
About the original story: In it, he identified the sitter as Lisa Gherardini, the wife of wealthy Florentine businessman Francesco del Giocondo. "Mona" was a common Italian contraction of " madonna," meaning "my lady," the equivalent of the English "Madam," so the title means "Madam Lisa".
